item.title: Sun, 27 Aug 2023 10:30:03 UTC
item.description:
Hi Folks!
Some python packages are missing. I ask you to be patient
a little as I am in a period of medical therapies and
time is short, and something escapes me.
For example nvchecker requires additional modules, which
used to install pip, but I noticed that using pip created
conflicts with system packages. I will add modules,
and others will be removed. With patience. Pardon.
Let me know which ones need care too. Thanks.

item.title: Wed, 23 Aug 2023 07:11:42 UTC
item.description:
Forgive me for too many mistakes these days
I have some problems with lua and with weechat.
With lua I had missed the change of include dir
(thanks to Julian for the report), and I have problem
with sbbdep reporting error (probably due to some
missing symlink that Pat does not use). I use sbbdep
to check that everything is ok with the dependencies,
and by reporting error I focused on something else
and lost sight of something else. With weechat I have
the problem that in my installations it crashes,
but some people have told me that they get it going,
but unfortunately I can't verify for the moment :/
Sorry for these errors and for my bad English. Thanks Deepl :)
